<div xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="trans-illegiblecharknown-pt-br" xml:lang="pt-br">
    <head>Caracteres Ilegíveis, Quantidade Conhecida </head>
    <p><!--gloss--></p>
    <p><specList>
            <specDesc key="gap"/>
        </specList>
        <!--<listRef>
            <ptr target="a"/>
            </listRef>--></p>
    <p>Noscasos onde há vestígios de caracteres, mas estres não podem ser reconhecidos e sua
        quantidade é conhecida, estes devem ser colocados dentro de uma tag <gi>gap</gi> e receber
        um atributo <att>reason</att> com o valor "illegible".</p>
    <cit>
        <!-- VIII.2 is a normal gap (characters lost, lacuna) - there is no Panciera section corresponding exactly to 'Illegible Characters, Quantity Known' but I think this would be rendered the same way -->
        <quote>[...]</quote>
        <bibl corresp="#panciera">
            <biblScope>VIII.2</biblScope>
        </bibl>
        <bibl corresp="#ddbdp"/>
        <!-- etc. -->
    </cit>
    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples" corresp="#panciera">
        <gap reason="illegible" quantity="3" unit="character"/>
    </egXML>
    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples" rend="london"
        corresp="http://inslib.kcl.ac.uk/irt2009/IRT690.html">
        <gap reason="illegible" quantity="1" unit="character"/>
    </egXML>
    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples" rend="ddbdp"
        corresp="http://papyri.info/ddbdp/bgu;1;101">
        <gap reason="illegible" quantity="2" unit="character"/>
    </egXML>
    <divGen type="seealso"/>
